#Bitcoin stands alone as an asset class. Lumping together all "Crypto" assets and BTC is simply doing it a huge disservice. #Bitcoin price might as well go to 5k or 10k this bear cycle (nobody knows) but it won't change the fact that BTC is a damn good store-of-value.

The downside of being a truly free market asset is that one can't stop #Bitcoin from being used as collateral for the myriad Ponzi Crypto schemes that will keep coming and going bust, taking BTC down along with them temporarily from time to time.

But #Bitcoin won't act like a store-of-value till more people appreciate this aspect of the asset. Its clear from recent price action that there are still way more speculators in BTC than people looking for an inflation hedge. How long will it take for more people to come around?

There were many wildly bullish takes on #Bitcoin when price was 60k and there are a lot of wildly pessimistic "told-you-so" takes on #Bitcoin now that price is 20k. But the algorithm remains the same irrespective of price. And that is the single most important thing about BTC
